com.pb.sawdust.util.parsing

Interface Parser<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type of input to be parsed.
    O - The output type of the parser.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayParser, BinaryParser, DelimitedDataParser, FixedWidthStringParser, ObjectArrayParser

    public interface Parser<I,O>
    The Parser interface is intended for use by classes which can take an input and transform (parse) it into an array of outputs. There is no requirement (nor expectation) that a given Parser<I,O> can parse e=every given input I; the method isParsable(I) is specified to give users access to the parsability of a given input.
